description:
&lt;p&gt;Swindon Intensive Team following a skill mix review are happy to be able to invite applications from Occupational Therapist for the role of specialist practitioner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will incorporate ring fenced time min 20% to undertake OT specific tasks in addition to bringing the OT perspective to the wider remit of the role and multi-disciplinary team functioning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The work within our Intensive services is varied, rewarding and fulfilling. The service provides a 24/7 - 365 day service. Intensive services contain a variety of multi-disciplinary roles including administration, Consultant Psychiatrist, Mental Health Nurses and Mental health Workers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The remit of the role is varied and will enable you to utilize your skills to work collaboratively with service users at a point of crisis. Intensive services work closely with a wide range of internal and external teams and agencies. Intensive services provide urgent care to provide an alternate to hospital admission or to supported hospital discharge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:  Emma Clack, Team Manager on emma.clack@nhs.net or 01793 836820&lt;/p&gt;
